CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 19, 1951, pg. 5 reads: "...ONS - Five generations of this...attend the Corinthian Baptist...which the Rev. H.S. Cuff is ...five members of the family...ng a differrent [different] generation,...Sunday. Left to right: Mrs. Lula Turner, James Turner, Mrs. Lula Mae Mott, Mrs. Fannie Mae Nelson and John Nelson, Jr.  Mrs. Turner, born in 1865, keeps house for her self and spends a lot of time with the sick and shut-ins. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, including, from left: possibly Lula Mae Mott, Lula Turner, John Nelson Jr, center; James Turner, and possibly Fannie Mae Nelson, posed in Corinthian Baptist Church, another version
